originalText.text:
I rented a decent apartment in a rundown building. The front door to the building had a defective lock and there were times I had to jiggle the key for half an hour before I could get in. I called Accredited Accommodations about that and they let the call go to the answering machine. They returned the call the next day and suggested that I wait until the following morning when their office was open. Big help!!!!! Not being able to get into the building is a MAJOR PROBLEM, one that really requires their attention.

I never heard from them again until my last evening there when they left a message changing the procedure by which I was to leave the keys for the owner.

I had to follow up with them to make sure that I got my security deposit back. They deducted $15 to pay their employee to go to the bank to make the deposit. That is THEIR cost of doing business, not mine. They also shorted me by a few dollars.

I WILL NEVER USE THIS AGENCY AGAIN!

originalText.text: Stay away from this place. When you try to rent from them they take only cash and ask you to give them  also your credit card as security. Once you leave they bill you for something you have not done. Shame on you. We are stopping our credit card. You cannot reach them over the phone and they do not return calls. We tried to reach them over 2 days and still no answer.
